refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
public DateTimeImmutableDateTimeImmutable::setTimestamp inttimestamp
Returns a new DateTimeImmutable object with the date and time set based on an Unix timestamp.

&reftitle.parameters;

 &date.datetime.description.modified;

  timestamp



    Unix timestamp representing the date.
    Setting timestamps outside the range of &integer; is possible by using
    DateTimeImmutable::modify with the @ format.

  &reftitle.examples;

   DateTimeImmutable::setTimestamp example

&style.oop;


<?php
$date = new DateTimeImmutable();
echo $date->format('U = Y-m-d H:i:s') . "\n";

$newDate = $date->setTimestamp(1171502725);
echo $newDate->format('U = Y-m-d H:i:s') . "\n";
?>


   &examples.outputs.similar;


1272508903 = 2010-04-28 22:41:43
1171502725 = 2007-02-14 20:25:25
